---
source: src/server.rs
expression: "schema_description_for(\"get_commit_history\")"
---
Returns one structured manifest per commit in a range, so agents can
see what changed in each commit separately. Use this instead of
`git log <base>..<head>` plus a per-commit `git show`, or
`gh pr view --json commits` — those return either prose summaries
or commit metadata without per-file change detail. This tool gives
you both at once: the commit (sha, author, subject, body) AND the
same structured per-file manifest `get_change_manifest` returns,
for every commit in the range.
Use this when you need to attribute a change to a specific commit —
reverting a regression, writing a CHANGELOG, or reasoning about
review feedback that calls out a specific sha. For "what is the
total diff between two refs?" use `get_change_manifest` instead;
it is cheaper and answers the same question without the per-commit
breakdown. Page size is bounded by the standard pagination cursor.
